## Accessibility

### Non-Negotiable

- Every interactive element must be keyboard-accessible: buttons, links, form inputs, modals, dropdowns
- Every `<img>` must have an `alt` attribute — decorative images use `alt=""`
- Color contrast: text must meet WCAG AA (4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text). Use design system tokens — they are pre-checked.
- Never use color alone to convey information — add an icon, label, or pattern
- Focus indicators must be visible — never `outline: none` without a replacement focus style
- Modals must trap focus inside and return focus to the trigger on close
- Forms: every input must have an associated `<label>` (visible or `sr-only`). Placeholder text is not a label.

### Semantic HTML

- Use `<button>` for actions, `<a>` (or React Router `<Link>`) for navigation — never `<div onClick>`
- Use heading hierarchy (`h1` → `h2` → `h3`) — don't skip levels for styling
- Use `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<aside>`, `<footer>` landmark elements
- Lists of items: use `<ul>` or `<ol>`, not a series of `<div>` elements

